definition: to do/to manage/to handle/to play with/to fool with/to mess with/to fix/to toy with
Qing or Ch'ing dynasty of imperial China (1644-1911)/surname Qing
clear/distinct/quiet/just and honest/pure/to settle or clear up/to clean up or purge

sentences.english: No one could account for the fact that one of the boxes was extremely heavy.
sentences.chinese: 此中有只箱子特别重，可谁也弄不清是怎么回事。

sentences.english: But the meaning of other symbols is not so clear, even to me.
sentences.chinese: 但是其他的符号就不太明显，甚至我自己也弄不清。

sentences.english: Daughter side, looked at his father's doubts about the his intention.
sentences.chinese: 女儿站在一边，疑惑地望着父亲，弄不清他的用意。

sentences.english: We were wondering whether to go today or tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 我们弄不清是今天走还是明天走。

sentences.english: Sometimes you just can't tell exactly what is going to work.
sentences.chinese: 有时候，你会弄不清究竟什么才能成功。

sentences.english: It was moving down the beach toward the water.
sentences.chinese: 他们弄不清这是什么动物。

sentences.english: I cannot sense your meaning sometimes.
sentences.chinese: 我有时候也弄不清你的用意。

sentences.english: He couldn't tell if she was laughing or crying.
sentences.chinese: 他弄不清她是笑还是哭。

to be unable to guess or make out
to remain puzzled after pondering over sth a hundred times (idiom)/to remain perplexed despite much thought
to not know the reason/to not know what to do
to be unable to make any sense of the matter/to be at a loss
amidst the clouds and mist/(fig.) mystified/puzzled
